HUGH FEARNLEY-WHITTINGSTALL: Of
course they are a suggestion.

00:32:52.750 --> 00:32:55.930
You know, used by I've
got a bit of a problem

00:32:55.930 --> 00:32:57.970
with because it's
quite a bossy thing.

00:32:57.970 --> 00:33:01.010
It's like suggesting you've
really got to do this thing.

00:33:01.010 --> 00:33:04.370
And I think a lot of
people-- and I didn't really

00:33:04.370 --> 00:33:06.370
realize this-- but when
we did the waste series,

00:33:06.370 --> 00:33:07.161
I talked to people.

00:33:07.161 --> 00:33:11.404
They actually felt
really compelled.

00:33:11.404 --> 00:33:12.820
I thought the
spinach looked fine,

00:33:12.820 --> 00:33:15.640
but it said used by
the 11th of March.

00:33:15.640 --> 00:33:19.600
So on the 11th of March
on the 10th of March even,

00:33:19.600 --> 00:33:20.980
I had to bin it.

00:33:20.980 --> 00:33:23.530
You really don't have to.

00:33:23.530 --> 00:33:28.770
The first thing to care
about is cooking foods.

00:33:28.770 --> 00:33:30.910
If a vegetable is
a little bit tired,

00:33:30.910 --> 00:33:33.206
you might not want
to eat them raw,

00:33:33.206 --> 00:33:35.080
but you can roast them
or make them into soup

00:33:35.080 --> 00:33:38.560
or put them together with
various other things.

00:33:38.560 --> 00:33:40.660
There's no real safety
issue of anything

00:33:40.660 --> 00:33:42.100
that's properly cooked.

00:33:42.100 --> 00:33:45.400
Anything that's heated above
70 degrees for three minutes

00:33:45.400 --> 00:33:48.070
is safe.

00:33:48.070 --> 00:33:50.230
But I have to say
one or two things,

00:33:50.230 --> 00:33:53.740
very few toxins
that don't survive--

00:33:53.740 --> 00:33:54.625
toxins not bacteria.

00:33:54.625 --> 00:33:56.560
All bacteriological
contamination

00:33:56.560 --> 00:34:01.501
is killed at 70 degrees
for a couple of minutes.

00:34:01.501 --> 00:34:03.070
No doubt about that at all.

00:34:03.070 --> 00:34:04.870
There's a few rather
unusual toxins

00:34:04.870 --> 00:34:08.812
that can appear in things
like fermented rice

00:34:08.812 --> 00:34:10.270
that has gone off
or beans that you

00:34:10.270 --> 00:34:12.770
have to be a little bit careful,
but that's a bit out there.

00:34:12.770 --> 00:34:15.590
Mostly, heating food
makes it really safe.

00:34:15.590 --> 00:34:17.989
So there's no really
real safety issue.

00:34:17.989 --> 00:34:21.375
So if it looks OK and it
tastes OK, what is the problem?

00:34:21.375 --> 00:34:23.500
MARIANA SARACENI: Back
home, we actually don't even

00:34:23.500 --> 00:34:24.458
