00:39:21.580 --> 00:39:22.930
If you've experimented with it.

00:39:22.930 --> 00:39:26.620
And if so, how do you see that
evolving into everyday kitchen?

00:39:26.620 --> 00:39:28.120
HUGH FEARNLEY-WHITTINGSTALL:
I think

00:39:28.120 --> 00:39:32.470
it's going to be
massive and important.

00:39:32.470 --> 00:39:34.140
It's a really good
source of protein.

00:39:34.140 --> 00:39:38.940
Of course, we've
eaten insects forever.

00:39:38.940 --> 00:39:40.900
Ever since we could
call ourselves

00:39:40.900 --> 00:39:45.280
any sort of a human being,
we've been insect eaters.

00:39:45.280 --> 00:39:49.090
