00:48:54.270 --> 00:48:55.061
AUDIENCE: Hi, Hugh.

00:48:55.061 --> 00:48:55.596
I'm Alex.

00:48:55.596 --> 00:48:56.970
I have a question
about children.

00:48:56.970 --> 00:48:58.810
You started talking
about it earlier.

00:48:58.810 --> 00:49:02.490
So I cook in my house, and my
wife used to be a vegetarian.

00:49:02.490 --> 00:49:04.830
So I used to cook pretty much
three meals-- kids' meals,

00:49:04.830 --> 00:49:07.500
my wife's meal, and my meal.

00:49:07.500 --> 00:49:09.280
I mean, I would love
all of these things,

00:49:09.280 --> 00:49:11.571
and I think my kids would
definitely like some of them.

00:49:11.571 --> 00:49:13.590
But there are, as you
said, some complex flavors

00:49:13.590 --> 00:49:15.420
and spices in here.

00:49:15.420 --> 00:49:17.700
How best can I get my
children-- who are young,

00:49:17.700 --> 00:49:19.320
two and a half and five--

00:49:19.320 --> 00:49:22.320
to start adventuring
more with their food

00:49:22.320 --> 00:49:27.530
and getting more sophisticated
palates at that kind of age?

00:49:27.530 --> 00:49:30.000
HUGH FEARNLEY-WHITTINGSTALL:
It's a really good question.

00:49:30.000 --> 00:49:32.460
Putting a lot of
stuff in front of kids

00:49:32.460 --> 00:49:34.780
early is really important--

00:49:34.780 --> 00:49:35.550
really early.

00:49:35.550 --> 00:49:37.175
I mean, I'm not saying
you're too late,

00:49:37.175 --> 00:49:39.570
but there is something that
kicks in with kids, which

00:49:39.570 --> 00:49:42.000
is that after a certain age--

00:49:42.000 --> 00:49:44.940
and it's usually the age when
they're independently mobile--

00:49:44.940 --> 00:49:46.824
they become a bit
mistrustful of new foods.

00:49:46.824 --> 00:49:48.240
And there's an
evolutionary reason

00:49:48.240 --> 00:49:51.420
for that, which is that,
once you wander away

00:49:51.420 --> 00:49:54.870
from the immediate control of
your parent figure, usually

00:49:54.870 --> 00:49:58.920
your mother, you don't want to
be popping berries and things

00:49:58.920 --> 00:50:00.390
randomly into your mouth.

00:50:00.390 --> 00:50:04.540
So a little bit of
protection kicks in.

00:50:04.540 --> 00:50:06.690
So you need to
encourage your children

00:50:06.690 --> 00:50:09.080
to recognize as many
different foods as possible

00:50:09.080 --> 00:50:10.470
are safe and exciting.

00:50:10.470 --> 00:50:13.390
Even if they don't necessarily
like them straightaway,

00:50:13.390 --> 00:50:15.721
it's important that they
know that they are food.

00:50:15.721 --> 00:50:17.970
And there's all sorts of
things I didn't like as a kid

00:50:17.970 --> 00:50:19.470
that I've somehow
come around to.

00:50:19.470 --> 00:50:21.690
Mushrooms, ugh, slimy,
revolting things.

00:50:21.690 --> 00:50:23.320
Now, I love them to bits.

00:50:23.320 --> 00:50:27.270
Tomatoes, couldn't go near
one, mainly because they used

00:50:27.270 --> 00:50:28.620
to be completely tasteless.

00:50:28.620 --> 00:50:30.570
Although I was addicted
to tomato ketchup,

00:50:30.570 --> 00:50:32.840
so there was kind of
a contradiction there.

00:50:32.840 --> 00:50:34.710
But it's about variety.

00:50:34.710 --> 00:50:37.440
It's about using spices
in a very subtle way

00:50:37.440 --> 00:50:39.390
to begin with because
kids actually do quite

00:50:39.390 --> 00:50:40.800
like a little bit of spice.

00:50:40.800 --> 00:50:42.300
Kids love garlic.

00:50:42.300 --> 00:50:44.680
A little bit of garlicky oil.

00:50:44.680 --> 00:50:47.680
Green beans and carrots
plainly steamed, fine.

00:50:47.680 --> 00:50:51.120
But if you cook a tiny
bit of garlic in oil

00:50:51.120 --> 00:50:53.130
or a little bit
of butter and you

00:50:53.130 --> 00:50:56.130
toss the vegetables in that,
that little savory edge

00:50:56.130 --> 00:50:56.674
makes it--

00:50:56.674 --> 00:50:58.590
there's something for
them to catch onto there

00:50:58.590 --> 00:51:00.540
that they often really like.

00:51:00.540 --> 00:51:03.570
So a little bit of
seasoning, not too much salt.

00:51:03.570 --> 00:51:06.450
Also, it's a bit of an easy
win salt. Kids do like salt,

00:51:06.450 --> 00:51:08.440
so you have to be a bit careful.

00:51:08.440 --> 00:51:12.210
But tiny bits of garlic,
very, very small amounts

00:51:12.210 --> 00:51:14.310
of curry powder
even can actually

00:51:14.310 --> 00:51:16.350
stimulate kids to
like vegetables

00:51:16.350 --> 00:51:18.790
more rather than less.

